---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="AI Guide — Mach 1 Business | Starling AIX"
  description="The AI-native enterprise is here. Are you ready for it? Download the free eBook and UCA Standard."
>

<!-- ── Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section style="position:relative;overflow:hidden;padding:7rem 0 6rem;" class="grid-bg">
  <div class="hero-glow"></div>
  <span class="corner-mark cm-tl">+</span>
  <span class="corner-mark cm-tr">+</span>
  <div class="container" style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:3rem;align-items:center;" class="guide-hero-grid">

      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">Starling AIX · Free eBook</p>
        <h1 class="heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.08"
            style="font-size:clamp(3rem,8vw,5.5rem);margin:0 0 1.5rem;letter-spacing:-0.04em;max-width:760px;">
          The AI-native enterprise is here. <em>Are you ready?</em>
        </h1>
        <p class="fade-up" data-delay="0.13" style="font-size:1.05rem;color:#71717a;line-height:1.75;max-width:520px;margin:0 0 0.75rem;">
          Claude connects to 50+ workplace tools. Agent teams run multi-step workflows. The outputs are Word docs, decks, and spreadsheets — not chat responses.
        </p>
        <p class="fade-up" data-delay="0.16" style="font-size:1rem;color:#71717a;line-height:1.75;max-width:520px;margin:0 0 2.5rem;">
          The question isn't whether AI will change your organisation. <em>It's whether you've got the architecture to handle it.</em>
        </p>
        <div class="fade-up" data-delay="0.2" style="display:flex;gap:0.75rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <a href="#download" class="btn btn-primary">Get the Free eBook →</a>
          <a href="/cognitive-design" class="btn btn-ghost">Build Your Org Brain</a>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:0.78rem;color:#3f3f46;margin-top:0.75rem;">Includes the complete UCA Standard · Download below</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Book mockup -->
      <div class="fade-up" data-delay="0.12" style="display:flex;justify-content:flex-start;">
        <div class="card-flat" style="width:220px;overflow:hidden;position:relative;">
          <div style="height:3px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,#f97316,#fb923c);"></div>
          <div style="padding:2rem 1.5rem 1.75rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;min-height:300px;justify-content:space-between;">
            <div>
              <span class="badge" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;display:inline-flex;font-size:0.62rem;">Contains the complete UCA Standard + Summon Starling</span>
              <h2 class="heading-upright" style="font-size:1.5rem;color:#fff;margin:0 0 0.4rem;line-height:1.2;">Mach 1 Business</h2>
              <p style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#71717a;margin:0 0 0.75rem;line-height:1.4;">Designing the Airframe for Industry 5.0</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.65rem;color:#3f3f46;margin:0;">Starling Press</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── The Real Problem ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">1.0 · The Real Problem</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          The tools work. The architecture doesn't.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          Every conversation with AI teaches the platform more about how your organisation thinks. If that intelligence lives on their servers, under their governance, improving their model — you're building someone else's asset.
        </p>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.13" style="margin-bottom:0;">
          Try switching AI vendors after a year of accumulated context. That's the trap. When the platform owns the memory, switching means starting from zero. The more you use it, the harder it is to leave.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.25rem;" class="problem-grid">
      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0" style="padding:2rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin:0 0 0.75rem;color:#fff;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-0.01em;">Who owns your knowledge?</h3>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">
          You've deployed AI and still get generic outputs. You've trained models on company knowledge. Built custom GPTs. Deployed agents that execute tasks but don't understand your business. Different teams re-teach the same context to different tools.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0.06" style="padding:2rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;margin:0 0 0.75rem;color:#fff;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-0.01em;">The HAL Architecture</h3>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">
          Your AI is a brilliant consultant, not a contextualised Chief of Staff. The intelligence is generic. The memory is theirs. The lock-in compounds over time. This is the Mach 1 Problem — and it has an architectural solution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── Search vs Address ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section" style="background:#030303;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">2.0 · The Solution</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          Search vs. Address.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          Every AI system today searches for your knowledge. That's the problem. Search burns tokens re-discovering context you already have. Addressing eliminates the cost entirely — O(1) lookup instead of O(n) search.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.25rem;" class="compare-grid">
      <div class="card-flat fade-up" data-delay="0" style="padding:2rem;border-left:3px solid #3f3f46;">
        <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;color:#52525b;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 1.25rem;">Search / RAG</p>
        <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.65rem;">
          {['Scattered data across platforms','Tangled connections, exponential complexity','Every query burns tokens re-discovering context','RAG hits a wall at enterprise volume','Token cost scales with organisational size'].map(t => (
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#71717a;padding-left:1rem;border-left:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);line-height:1.6;">{t}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card-flat fade-up" data-delay="0.06" style="padding:2rem;border-left:3px solid #f97316;">
        <p style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;color:#f97316;letter-spacing:0.08em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 1.25rem;">Address / UCA</p>
        <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.65rem;">
          {['Organised knowledge in semantic coordinates','Permanent addresses, instant retrieval','Constant time regardless of scale','O(1) lookup replaces O(n) search','The output is head code — canonical context your agents reference'].map(t => (
            <li style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#a1a1aa;padding-left:1rem;border-left:1px solid rgba(249,115,22,0.2);line-height:1.6;">{t}</li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── Who This Is For ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section" style="position:relative;" class="grid-bg">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">3.0 · Who This Is For</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          Leaders who want AI that compounds.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          You're watching platforms rise and fall, vendors pivot overnight, and last year's best practice become this year's technical debt. You need architecture that outlasts the tools. You don't need a technical background — you need to understand what's happening and ask the right questions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:1.25rem;" class="for-grid">
      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0" style="padding:2rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size:1.05rem;margin:0 0 0.75rem;color:#fff;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-0.01em;">You've deployed AI and still get generic outputs.</h3>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.875rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">
          You've built custom GPTs. Deployed agents that execute tasks but don't understand your business. Your AI is a brilliant consultant — not a contextualised Chief of Staff. The architecture is the gap.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card fade-up" data-delay="0.06" style="padding:2rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size:1.05rem;margin:0 0 0.75rem;color:#fff;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-0.01em;">You need AI that knows <em>your</em> domain.</h3>
        <p style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.875rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">
          Not a search engine with memory. A productivity booster that compounds your knowledge — where every session builds on the last, and the intelligence belongs to you. That's what this book explains.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── What You Get ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">4.0 · What You Get</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          Mach 1 Business.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          The architecture guide for AI-native organisations. This book names the forces breaking enterprise AI, introduces the Domain Language Model, and includes the complete Universal Cognitive Architecture Standard as a working appendix. It's also a dataset — load it into your AI and summon Starling.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Book contents as wide-mock -->
    <div class="wide-mock fade-up" data-delay="0.16">
      <div class="mock-bar">
        <span class="mock-dot r"></span><span class="mock-dot y"></span><span class="mock-dot g"></span>
        <span style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.7rem;color:#3f3f46;margin-left:0.75rem;">Mach 1 Business — Table of Contents</span>
        <span class="badge badge-neutral" style="margin-left:auto;">Free Download</span>
      </div>
      {[
        ['Part I','Why Enterprise AI Fails','Business has never had canon. The NL/JSON handoff point. Why 95% of enterprise AI pilots fail — and why the problem is architecture, not intelligence.'],
        ['Part II','The Domain Language Model','The DLM equation. O(1) semantic addressing vs. O(n) search. Information sovereignty. 3P0 Architecture — you own the memory, AI remains stateless.'],
        ['Part III','Unlocking Organisational Intelligence','Smart OS activation at 23 memories. The Constitutional 28 that complete organisational wholeness. Three paths from this book to a working Org Brain.'],
        ['Appendix A','Universal Cognitive Architecture','The complete UCA Standard. 11 Organisational Cognates, four memory tiers, semantic addressing protocol, the Constitutional 28, and the AI Processing Directive. CC BY 4.0.'],
        ['Appendix B','Summon Starling','The book installs itself. Upload to any AI, type "Starling," and activate an AI Chief of Staff that understands semantic addressing. Five minutes to organisational intelligence.'],
      ].map(([label, title, body], i, arr) => (
        <div style={`padding:1.5rem 2rem;display:grid;gap:0;${i < arr.length - 1 ? 'border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);' : ''}`} class="book-row">
          <div style="display:flex;gap:1.5rem;align-items:flex-start;">
            <span style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.7rem;color:#f97316;min-width:72px;padding-top:2px;">{label}</span>
            <div>
              <p style="font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:600;color:#e4e4e7;margin:0 0 0.3rem;letter-spacing:-0.01em;">{title}</p>
              <p style="font-size:0.825rem;color:#52525b;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">{body}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── iPub ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="feat-section" style="background:#030303;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feat-header">
      <!-- Left -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">5.0 · The Learning System</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06">
          What's an iPub?
        </h2>
      </div>
      <!-- Right -->
      <div>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          Books that double as datasets. You read the narrative — your AI reads the architecture. iPubs are a new kind of business book: each one teaches a framework, produces strategic outputs, and functions as a plug-in for your AI.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;" class="fade-up" data-delay="0.14">
      {[
        ['Chapters','Narrative + Framework','The argument. Proprietary business frameworks taught through guided discovery. You read to understand — your AI reads to process.'],
        ['Appendix A','Always included · The Standard','The open specification. Machine-readable architecture your AI uses to classify, address, and govern organisational knowledge.'],
        ['Appendix B','Always included · The Installer or Wake Word','Machine-executable logic. In the full library, this is the guided extraction sequence. In Mach 1 Business, it\'s the Summon Starling protocol.'],
        ['Appendix C','When applicable · The Worked Example','A complete reference implementation. Shows what the output looks like when the installer runs against real organisational data.'],
      ].map(([label, title, body], i, arr) => (
        <div style={`background:#0a0a0a;padding:1.5rem 2rem;display:flex;gap:1.5rem;align-items:flex-start;${i < arr.length - 1 ? 'border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);' : ''}`}>
          <span style="font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:0.68rem;color:#3f3f46;min-width:80px;padding-top:2px;">{label}</span>
          <div>
            <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;color:#e4e4e7;margin:0 0 0.3rem;letter-spacing:-0.01em;">{title}</p>
            <p style="font-size:0.825rem;color:#71717a;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">{body}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="divider"></div>

<!-- ── Download CTA ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section id="download" class="feat-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="cta-row">
      <div>
        <p class="feat-num fade-up" data-delay="0">6.0 · Get Started</p>
        <h2 class="feat-h2 heading-display fade-up" data-delay="0.06" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
          Get the book.
        </h2>
        <p class="feat-body fade-up" data-delay="0.1">
          Download Mach 1 Business free — including the complete UCA Standard and the Summon Starling appendix. You'll also receive the newsletter <em>On Cognitive Design</em> with insights on organisational intelligence.
        </p>
        <form id="dl-form" class="fade-up" data-delay="0.14"
              style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.75rem;max-width:400px;">
          <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Email address" required class="input" />
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;padding:0.75rem;">
            Download Free
          </button>
        </form>
        <p style="font-size:0.78rem;color:#3f3f46;margin-top:0.75rem;">Delivered immediately as PDF. No spam.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="glass fade-up" data-delay="0.12" style="padding:2.5rem;">
        <p class="feat-num" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem;">After the book, three paths</p>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">
          {[
            { label: 'Start Free', title: 'Appendix B — Summon Starling', body: 'Upload the book to Claude. Type "Starling." Get an AI Chief of Staff in five minutes.', href: '#download', btn: 'Download Now' },
            { label: 'Build Yourself', title: 'Cognitive Design Accelerator', body: 'Nine-week guided program. Build your Org Brain, get certified.', href: '/cognitive-design', btn: 'See the Curriculum' },
            { label: 'Have Us Build It', title: 'Enterprise Services', body: 'Starling builds your Org Brain directly. Every engagement ends with a certified person.', href: '/services', btn: 'Talk to Us' },
          ].map(({ label, title, body, href, btn }) => (
            <div style="padding:1rem;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-radius:8px;">
              <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;margin-bottom:0.4rem;">
                <span class="badge badge-neutral">{label}</span>
                <span style="font-size:0.825rem;color:#e4e4e7;font-weight:500;">{title}</span>
              </div>
              <p style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#52525b;margin:0 0 0.65rem;line-height:1.6;">{body}</p>
              <a href={href} class="btn btn-ghost" style="font-size:0.75rem;padding:0.3rem 0.75rem;">{btn}</a>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
  @media(min-width:768px) {
    .guide-hero-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 260px !important; }
    .problem-grid    { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr !important; }
    .compare-grid    { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr !important; }
    .for-grid        { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr !important; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  document.getElementById('dl-form')?.addEventListener('submit', e => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const btn = (e.target as HTMLFormElement).querySelector('button') as HTMLButtonElement;
    btn.textContent = 'Check your email!';
    btn.disabled = true;
    setTimeout(() => { btn.textContent = 'Download Free'; btn.disabled = false; (e.target as HTMLFormElement).reset(); }, 4000);
  });
</script>
